1 olive oil
1 packet pork loin steaks
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 bag chives
1 tomato
1 cucumber
½ bottle cream
1 bag salad leaves
1 packet Balsamic & Olive Oil Dressing
1 packet Roasted Potatoes with Garlic Herb Butter
1 bag Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over medium-high heat
• Cook pork and seasoning, until cooked through, 3-4 mins each side
• Transfer to plate, cover and rest for 5 mins
• Finely chop chives. Chop tomato and cucumber

• Prick a few holes in potato packet. Microwave until soft and steaming,  4-5 mins
• Return pan to medium-low heat with a drizzle of oil. Add cream (1/2 bottle for 2P / 1 bottle for 4P) and chives and cook until slightly reduced, 1-2 mins
• Remove pan from heat and stir through cheese

• In a bowl, combine tomato, cucumber, salad leaves and dressing. Season
• Plate up potato, pork and salad
• Spoon sauce over pork to serve